EMERGENCY crews are dealing with a crash involving a lorry and a car on the M90 in Perthshire.
The collision, between Bridge of Earn and Perth, caused a fuel spillage and has closed a lane of the southbound carriageway.
It is understood the lorry crashed into the central reservation, followed by a black Citroen C5 just after 10am.
No one was injured in the smash but long tailbacks are expected on approach to the scene.
The Scottish Fire and Rescue Service are dealing with the fuel spillage and work is being carried out to repair the damaged barriers before the road can reopen.
 

